body: Hello Chien, I checked your 'Getting Started with Honeybee and OpenStudio' video at youtube (Cheers, thanks for bringing that videos out to the community!), and recreate the setup in my computer to run a simulation, this was I got: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/Vfj0TqHwhivbkwYXo3FmaKDD8zYRhyAG87WQNb2hW-7DmjZI5*6HyHDay6Ta*bk*afUNDG3o8C595smaOWoNBiqrLI6BJn-v/1SystemsSetup.png)[](http://api.ning.com:80/files/Vfj0TqHwhisrJduI3I*8rSZsBLX-9slecWhuvhy3h2pEWOewY5xRQc8fCzmmuLJnpJ2ABCsfj8KTpvdMv6RpMaSK7O5w42u6/1SystemsSetupZoom.png)

replies.body: Hi Alejandro. This is a question for Chien Si but before he gets back to you I wanted to make sure that you are using the latest version from Github. He is updating the components frequently these days.
Hi Mostapha,  yes, I updated to the latest version before the run.

Hi again Chien, Yes for the explanation of the underlying issue, it makes it clear. I´ve running some tests with the updated component and the simulations are running ok now :) Yet a new hurdle I encountered is that the 'Read EP Result' cannot find the csv file with the results. I checked the file path and they don´t appear to be there as if the simulation hadn´t run. Do you have any thoughts on that? Thanks, Alejandro [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/qmsUgHzH5lN6h6e4M9l-9mAEa3u9NLLSMYqrJjUZbiolQcT85ptz5XGT7YCxCWUWkAnvMz8w0T7vulnaauyQNEUYW6n6eaWf/LBHB01SkyRiseSetup2message.png)

Hi again Chien, Hey I went back to the issue of retreiving the results from a "5.Packaged VAV w/Reheat" run I had in the past, and I´m still not getting a CSV with the results from the simulation. Do you have an idea of what might be going on (I working with the latest updates)? Thanks, Alejandro [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/Lf1B3Uv2G4t1jQlDiaZGhKrKEbYDZO2QecZ4*sBrnO8EHAF-Bi-m6iR3GX*AGjNKdWyDSWuoe0avssxZodyqgPuzmWVEQf3a/IssueReadingResults2.png) [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/Lf1B3Uv2G4vmLKMGHiVTanY4ST*s5LiLTMoGsaHWTJqApq83xp*2CqIXgtGLgApr*jidYJmfZXNl9jBGasJnl8wZNTDH4DOz/IssueReadingResults.png)

Hi Alejandro,

Is this issue solved. If not I would submit it as an issue to github so Chris can take a look. He is the one who developed the results reader.

Mostapha

Hi Mostpha,

The issue is still unresolved. Here I attach the definition with the latest LBHB version.

If further information is needed please let me know.

Thanks,

Alejandro
